reactions in niobium in the energy range 30-80-MeV.

x4codes.hlp: M.S. University of Baroda, Baroda, India

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Jour. of Physics, Part G (Nucl.and Part.Phys.), Vol.22, p.1455 (1996)

x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
Spectroscopically purity 99.99% niobium foils of
thickness 22 mg/cm**2 were interspersed with aluminium
foils of varying thickness acting as energy degraders.
.Pre-equilibrium hybrid model.

x4codes.hlp: Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre, Kolkata, India

x4freetext: Irradiaion time was about 1.5 hours.
Each stack consisted up to 52 single foils.
Beam current of the order of 200 nanoampers.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.27, p.431 (1976)

x4freetext: The total error includes the uncertainty in the
thickness of aluminium foils, the efficiency of the
detector, the beam current, the angular straggling and
the statistical error in the analysis of gamma rays.
